Setting up a new repo.

1. Got to github.com
2. Setup the new repo: here progdocs.
3. Set up the new folder. Here SysProgDocs/progdocs
4. Go to the folder
3. Paste or create new docs.
4. git clone git://github.com/beaucoder/progdocs.git
5. git add .
6. git commit -m "Initial progdocs for Rails & Git."
7. git remote add progdocs https://github.com/beaucoder/progdocs.git
8. git push --set-upstream progdocs master
9. git staus  -- should now be clean.
10. Going to GitHub progdocs should correctly show all commits.

Phew!!!  Finally getting there!!.

Accidental deletion??  One or many files??

First do git ls-files -d   for list deleted files.
then do 
		git ls_files -d | xargs git checkout -- pipes the deleted to checkout.
